{
  "texts": [
    "For example, non-verbal communication in humans [7] transmits qualitative information related to emotions.",
    "Facial and corporal signals are fast to transmit but do not provide details about the elicitor of the emotions.",
    "They get meaning from the context in which they are transmitted.",
    "The context of the emitter and receiver may differ, creating fuzzy qeios.com doi.org/10.32388/2RBRWN.4information causing fuzzy communication [8] or even misinformation.",
    "Misinformation related to emotions, values, and religion is often a source of con ict and even war."
  ]
}